      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "T5 to T2 is a relatively short walk, about 10-15 minutes, which is a bit of a relief. You can easily take the Tube (London Underground) from T5 to Heathrow Central, and then walk to T2. It's a straightforward journey, and the Tube is a convenient way to get around the airport.\n\nAs for security lines, LHR can get busy, especially during peak travel times. However, the security procedures are generally efficient, and you can expect to wait no more than 30-45 minutes in a typical queue. It's a bit like waiting in line for a popular restaurant, but with fewer people and more comfortable seating. Just be prepared to take off your shoes, belts, and electronics, and to have your liquids and gels in a clear, quart-sized bag.\n\nIf you do get stuck in a long line, you can try to make the most of it by grabbing a snack or drink from one of the airport's many cafes or shops. And if you're feeling anxious, you can take a deep breath and remind yourself that it's just a minor delay. After all, the airport is designed to handle crowds and delays, and it's all part of the journey. Just",
